        {
            "id": "s_l1_8",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "The Modulo Operator % 🔄",
            "content": "# Finding Remainders\n\nModulo (`%`) gives the **remainder** after division:\n\n* `17 % 5` → `2` (17 ÷ 5 = 3 remainder **2**)\n* `10 % 3` → `1` (10 ÷ 3 = 3 remainder **1**)\n* `8 % 4` → `0` (8 ÷ 4 = 2 remainder **0**)\n\nSuper useful for checking even/odd!"
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l1_9",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Modulo in Action 💻",
            "content": "See practical uses of modulo:",
            "codeSnippet": "# Check if even or odd\nnum = 7\nif num % 2 == 0:\n    print(num, \"is even\")\nelse:\n    print(num, \"is odd\")\n\n# Time conversion\ntotal_minutes = 135\nhours = total_minutes // 60\nminutes = total_minutes % 60\nprint(f\"{total_minutes} min = {hours}h {minutes}m\")",
            "codeLanguage": "python",
            "canRunCode": true
        },
