            "title": "Exponentiation ** 📈",
            "content": "# Powers Made Easy\n\nUse `**` for exponents (powers):\n\n* `2 ** 3` → `8` (2³ = 2×2×2)\n* `10 ** 2` → `100` (10²)\n* `5 ** 0` → `1` (anything to power 0)\n* `9 ** 0.5` → `3.0` (square root!)"
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l1_12",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Powers and Roots 💻",
            "content": "Calculate powers and roots:",
            "codeSnippet": "print(\"2^3 =\", 2 ** 3)      # 8\nprint(\"10^4 =\", 10 ** 4)    # 10000\nprint(\"2^10 =\", 2 ** 10)    # 1024\n\n# Square roots\nprint(\"√25 =\", 25 ** 0.5)   # 5.0\nprint(\"√2 =\", 2 ** 0.5)     # 1.414...\n\n# Cube root\nprint(\"∛27 =\", 27 ** (1/3)) # 3.0",
            "codeLanguage": "python",
            "canRunCode": true
        },
